com.quest.glue.api.services
Interface AgentMetadataService2

All Superinterfaces:
Service
public interface AgentMetadataService2
extends Service

This service provides information about the currently running agent. Typically this will be information that is contained in the agent's manifest file.

Since:
5.5.5.5

Method Detail

getFullInstanceName

java.lang.String getFullInstanceName()
Returns the fully qualified instance name for this agent instance. This is composed of the agent package, type and the name of this particular instance of the agent.

Returns:
the full instance name for this agent as a String.

getFullTypeName

java.lang.String getFullTypeName()
Returns the fully qualified type of the agent. The type will be something like "OSCartridges/Log_Filter" for all instances of the Log_Filter agent.

Returns:
the full agent type name of this agent

getInstanceId

java.util.UUID getInstanceId()
Get the ID for this agent instance. This ID is specific to the current FglAM instance and is distinct from the cagentID value in the Agent topology object.

Returns:
A UUID that uniquely identifies this agent instance.

getLastSampleSubmissionDate

java.util.Date getLastSampleSubmissionDate()
Gets the Date the last data sample was submitted by this agent instance. This will be null if no data samples have been submitted.

Returns:
The last sample submission date or null if no samples have been submitted.

getNumDataSamplesSubmitted

long getNumDataSamplesSubmitted()
Gets the number of data sample submitted by this agent since it was created.

Returns:
the number of data sample submitted since the agent was created.

getPackageBuildID

java.lang.String getPackageBuildID()
Gets the build ID (build number) for this agent's package.

Returns:
the build ID

getPackageName

java.lang.String getPackageName()
Get the name of the package containing this agent.

Returns:
String name of the package

getPackageVersion

java.lang.String getPackageVersion()
Get the version number for this agent's package

Returns:
the version string

getUnqualifiedInstanceName

java.lang.String getUnqualifiedInstanceName()
Get the unqualified instance name for this agent. Note that instance names are only unique within a given agent type.

Returns:
the unqualified instance name for this agent as a String

getUnqualifiedTypeName

java.lang.String getUnqualifiedTypeName()
Return the unqualified type name of the agent. Note that type names are only unique within a given package.

Returns:
the unqualified type of the agent

isAsynchronous

boolean isAsynchronous()
Whether or not the agent is set to run asynchronously. Asynchronous agents are expected to allow multiple execution threads, while non-asynchronous agents will be single threaded.

Refer to the "Thread Safety" section of the developer's manual for more details about single- versus multi-threaded agent behavior.

Returns:
true if the agent is running asynchronously and false if it is not.

isOutOfProcess

boolean isOutOfProcess()
Is this agent's package configured to be run out of process?

Returns:
boolean out of process status
